    "context": "Maria Santini, a renowned opera singer, is known for her powerful and captivating performances in multiple languages. Born in Italy, she is of Italian descent and began her musical education at the prestigious Milan Conservatory of Music. Maria is fluent in several languages including Italian, French, German, and English, enabling her to perform a wide range of operatic pieces in their original languages. With her exceptional talent, Maria has enchanted audiences around the world with her melodic voice and emotional depth. She is a citizen of Italy and often sings in her native language as well as other languages to connect with diverse audiences. Throughout her career, Maria Santini has been praised for her ability to convey the emotional nuances of the original language of the works she performs, making her a highly respected figure in the opera world."
